Stenoptilia stigmatodactylus is a moth of the family Pterophoridae. It is found in western, central and Mediterranean Europe, extending into Asia Minor and North Africa. It is also known from Iran, Russia and Armenia.The wingspan is 17â€“23 mm.The larvae feed on Thymus vulgaris, Scabiosa ochroleuca, Scabiosa lucida and Knautia arvensis. They feed on the flowers and seeds. Pupation takes place on the stem of the host plant. The pupa is covered with a loose web.